HEADWORD: Graticule
<hw>Grat"i*cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Graticulation.</er>]</ety> <def>A design or draught which has been
divided into squares, in order to reproduce it in other
dimensions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gratification</ent>⟦br⟧
